<item>
            <title>[SPARK-2526] Simplify make-distribution.sh to just pass through Maven options</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-2526</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a some complexity make-distribution.sh around selecting profiles. This is both annoying to maintain and also limits the number of ways that packagers can use this. For instance, it&apos;s not possible to build with separate HDFS and YARN versions, and supporting this with our current flags would get pretty complicated. We should just allow the user to pass a list of profiles directly to make-distribution.sh - the Maven build itself is already parameterized to support this. We also now have good docs explaining the use of profiles in the Maven build.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All of this logic was more necessary when we used SBT for the package build, but we haven&apos;t done that for several versions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
